<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUN 94 / 'Brain drain' in science continues
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The 'brain drain' of scientists continues unabated, with one in five of the
UK's recently qualified PhD scientists going overseas for further study or
employment, the Institute of Manpower Studies says today.
The IMS found, however, that UK industry is suffering no shortage of
high-quality scientists, while unemployment levels for recently qualified
PhDs are only about 3 per cent.
