<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUN 94 / Labour 'would have devalued sterling'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Neil Kinnock, the former Labour leader, has said that he would have
devalued sterling in the exchange rate mechanism had his party won the last
general election.
In an interview for Channel 4, to be broadcast on Wednesday, Mr Kinnock says
Labour had to maintain 'an impression' during the 1992 campaign that it
would not devalue. But it would have abandoned the commitment because of the
need to pull Britain out of recession, he says.
