<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUN 94 / Northern travel group collapses
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sunseeker Leisure, a Huddersfield-based tour operator, collapsed at the
weekend. The Civil Aviation Authority said the company had 10,000 forward
bookings when it ceased trading.
Between 4,000 and 4,500 holidaymakers abroad when the collapse occurred will
be flown home by other operators.
There had been reports that the company was seeking re-financing after
experiencing cashflow problems.
