FT  13 JUN 94 / GMB will state Labour poll choice
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR, Labour Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The GMB general union, Labour's second-largest affiliated union, is expected
this week to endorse one of the candidates for the party leadership.
The three leading candidates are to speak today at the union's conference in
Blackpool. Mrs Margaret Beckett, acting leader, will address the conference,
and Mr Tony Blair and Mr John Prescott will speak at a rally for dele-gates.
Mr John Edmonds, general secretary, said yesterday that the union's choice
would be decided in time to meet the party's deadline of midnight on
Thursday.
The GMB has 836,000 members of whom 749,000 pay the political levy and are
therefore entitled to vote in the ballot for the Labour leadership.
Papers sent to members in the union's postal ballot - conducted by the
Electoral Reform Society - will be accompanied by a separate document
stating its choice for leader.
The union's ballot papers will be distributed by post on June 27 and the
ballot will close on July 18.
Mr Edmonds said the creation of full employment should be the issue that
decides Labour's leadership election.
Jobs and employment were the party's 'distinctive issue', he said. 'Jobs and
how to create them is the common platform of a candidate for Labour's
leader, making full employment the vision of the next Labour govern-ment.'
