<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 94 / Midland Bank stops taking smaller rivals' cash cards
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BETHAN HUTTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Midland Bank has dealt a blow to some of its smaller competitors in the Visa
credit card market by blocking the use of their customers' cards in its cash
machine network.
None of the issuers affected - Robert Fleming/Save &amp; Prosper, MBNA, and HFC
Bank, which runs the GM Card for Vauxhall - has its own cash machines.
HFC Bank said it had been given some warning that access to cashpoints was
going to be withdrawn, but neither Robert Fleming nor MBNA had been
notified.
Midland said the decision was 'purely commercial'. It had not notified all
the banks affected because they had not formally applied to join the
network. The move could be seen as a direct attack on some of Midland's most
serious rivals in the increasingly competitive UK credit card market. All
three issuers involved have been attracting much new business recently by
offering a range of incentives.
Robert Fleming is the worst affected bank, because the Visa network is used
not only by its credit card holders but also its current-account customers,
who use Visa cards as debit cards to access their accounts.
A Robert Fleming representative said the company was particularly upset that
it had not been informed of the decision, even after it came into effect,
and would be taking the issue up with the Hong Kong and Shanghai Bank,
owners of Midland. HFC Bank said it was not unduly concerned at the change
as cash withdrawals were only a peripheral part of its credit card
facilities and not used by the majority of customers.
Visa said that although all banks in the Visa network were obliged to accept
foreign-issued cards in their machines, they were entitled to reject cards
issued by local competitors if they chose, and if this was made clear on the
machines.
Midland has not yet changed the logo on its machines to indicate that not
all Visa cards are accepted.
NatWest has never accepted Visa cards issued by anyone except itself,
Midland, TSB and foreign banks. Lloyds accepts all cards bearing the Visa
logo, and Barclays accepts all cards except the GM Card.
</TEXT>
