<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Equity derivatives bubbled into life with a rise in volume and a robust
performance by the June FT-SE contract against cash, writes Christine
Buckley.
Open interest - positions in the market - has increased and yesterday one
market specialist said the direction of least resistance had proved upwards.
June closed at a 6 point discount to cash although it had kept closer pace
for most of the session. Volume was a fairly strong 15,181 contracts.
Put buying was said to have been strong in options which indicates dealers
may be preparing for a fall in prices.
