<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black pepper prices continued to rise this week, in contrast to those for
white pepper, which suffered from a lack of buying support, reports Man
Producten. The black ASTA grades remained steady from most origins, like
Indonesia, India, Malaysia and Brazil. But faq grades went up sharply in
response to to strong demand from Singapore, Japan and the Middle East. In
the US market spot Indian black pepper rose to 88 cents a pound, June/July
shipment to 84 cents. In Europe the faq grade increased to Dollars 1,650
tonne. ASTA was traded at Dollars 1,825, spot, Rotterdam. Other spice were
generally unchanged.
