FT  11 JUN 94 / International Company News: Share placement by MIM Holdings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MIM Holdings, the Queensland-based metals and mining group, yesterday
announced a ADollars 416.8m (USDollars 306m) placement of new shares - the
first time in six years that the company has raised new capital via an
equity issue.
The shares being placed represent just under 10 per cent of MIM's issued
share capital.
The issue price was pitched at ADollars 2.925, a discount of more than 9 per
cent to Thursday night's closing price of ADollars 3.22. MIM shares fell six
cents, to ADollars 3.16, on news of the placement.
Mr Norm Fussell, MIM's managing director, said the funds would be used 'for
general corporate purposes, including the growth of the group's copper
business'.
The company has two important projects due to come on stream in the mid to
late 1990s: Ernest Henry, the rich copper-gold deposit in Australia, in
which MIM has a 51 per cent interest, and the Bajo de la Alumbrera deposit
in Argentina, in which MIM has a 50 per cent interest.
