<HEADLINE>
FT  11 JUN 94 / International Company News: Balsam files for bankruptcy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Balsam, the sports-surfaces company pushed into crisis after the arrest of
its entire board this week, filed for bankruptcy on Friday in the second
financial scandal to hit Germany in the past two months, Reuter reports from
Frankfurt.
The crash has also put at risk the future of Procedo, Germany's largest
export financing group.
Balsam was Procedo's biggest client, and bankers say that up to 75 per cent
of invoices it took as collateral on loans to Balsam may be worthless.
Procedo owes banks more than DM1.5bn (Dollars 899.6m).
