FT  11 JUN 94 / Markham Main pit to reopen
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Markham Main colliery in South Yorkshire, which was closed by British Coal
in 1992, will be producing coal again by the winter.
Coal Investments, a company headed by former British Coal commercial
director Mr Malcolm Edwards, has taken over the pit near Doncaster on a
15-year lease and expects to start recruiting in August.
About 150 miners will be employed initially and a further 100 jobs may
follow. Coal Investments has already been granted licences to run four pits
in Stoke, Coventry and south Wales.
