FT  11 JUN 94 / Poultry plant to create 450 jobs
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sun Valley Poultry, the convenience-foods manufacturer, is to spend Pounds
32m on a food-processing plant at Wolverhampton, West Midlands, creating 450
jobs over four years, Paul Cheeseright writes.
The plant, part of a Pounds 100m expansion programme, is expected to open in
May.
Sun Valley Poultry is a subsidiary of Cargill, the US foods and agriculture
group. It will use the plant to process poultry either as branded products
or as own-label lines for retailers.
The plan is thought to be the largest single investment in the Wolverhampton
area for 60 years and is a fillip to the gradual restructuring of the local
economy away from heavy industry and engineering.
Sun Valley is receiving Pounds 2.75m of regional selective assistance from
the Department of Trade and Industry.
