<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 94 / Visitors passport may be scrapped
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The British visitors passport may disappear as a result of a review of its
future being conducted by the government, Alan Pike writes.
The review has been prompted by warnings from the Spanish government that it
intends to cease recognising Britain's one-year travel document. No date for
the Spanish action has yet been announced - but British officials believe it
could take effect at the end of next year.
This suggests that a decision on whether to withdraw the British visitors
passport is likely to be taken before the end of this year.
The government is seeking the views of the travel trade and a range of other
interested groups as part of the review, which will be completed by the end
of the summer.
Ministers are likely to begin considering whether the British visitors
passport should be withdrawn, and other possible implications for the
issuing of passports, in the autumn.
</TEXT>
