<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUN 94 / Lisbon 'fastest growing city'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GILLIAN TETT, Economics Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Lisbon is set to be the fastest-growing European city in the next four
years, closely followed by Dublin, Hamburg, Athens and Lille, according to
new UK economic study.
The report, by Cambridge Econometrics, predicts Stuttgart will see the
slowest rate of economic growth. Stuttgart's economy is predicted to expand
by only 1.1 per cent a year, while Lisbon is expected to grow by 3.6 per
cent a year. London will grow 2.3 per cent a year, with Paris' growth rate
of 1.8 per cent.
European Regional Prospects; Cambridge Econometrics, Covent Garden,
Cambridge, UK. Ecu100
